WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.491 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.491 --> 00:00:07.485 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIO LOGO]

00:00:07.485 --> 00:00:22.954 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.954 --> 00:00:25.948 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:25.948 --> 00:01:00.379 align:middle line:90%


00:01:00.379 --> 00:01:05.080 align:middle line:10%
>> Researchers in Turkey are
about to embark on an excavation

00:01:05.080 --> 00:01:07.540 align:middle line:10%
at the ancient site
of Karahan Tepe,

00:01:07.540 --> 00:01:10.480 align:middle line:10%
and they believe it's much
older than Gobekli Tepe,

00:01:10.480 --> 00:01:13.580 align:middle line:10%
the famous zero point
of world history.

00:01:13.580 --> 00:01:16.870 align:middle line:84%
If you were to ask any
professor of history or even

00:01:16.870 --> 00:01:19.420 align:middle line:84%
a self-respecting
armchair archeologist

00:01:19.420 --> 00:01:22.780 align:middle line:84%
to name the oldest monument ever
discovered, they would have all

00:01:22.780 --> 00:01:24.340 align:middle line:90%
said Gobekli Tepe.

00:01:24.340 --> 00:01:27.790 align:middle line:84%
But now, that answer
might be Karahan Tepe.

00:01:27.790 --> 00:01:30.250 align:middle line:84%
And this is creating
a lot of excitement

00:01:30.250 --> 00:01:31.633 align:middle line:90%
in archeological circles.

00:01:31.633 --> 00:01:44.910 align:middle line:90%


00:01:44.910 --> 00:01:48.960 align:middle line:84%
Karahan Tepe is said to be
much older than Gobekli Tepe.

00:01:48.960 --> 00:01:52.050 align:middle line:84%
Archeologists have been
working at the Karahan Tepe

00:01:52.050 --> 00:01:55.860 align:middle line:84%
site, which is often called
the sister site of Gobekli Tepe

00:01:55.860 --> 00:01:58.140 align:middle line:90%
since 1997.

00:01:58.140 --> 00:02:03.300 align:middle line:84%
The site is located near
Yagmurlu and roughly 35 east

00:02:03.300 --> 00:02:06.350 align:middle line:84%
of the 12,000 year
old Gobekli Tepe site.

00:02:06.350 --> 00:02:11.940 align:middle line:90%


00:02:11.940 --> 00:02:14.220 align:middle line:84%
Over the years,
archeologists have

00:02:14.220 --> 00:02:16.320 align:middle line:84%
made a series of
amazing discoveries

00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:19.590 align:middle line:84%
that the Karahan Tepe
site, in particular,

00:02:19.590 --> 00:02:23.280 align:middle line:84%
tons of buried T-shaped
obelisks, similar to the ones

00:02:23.280 --> 00:02:25.900 align:middle line:84%
carved with wild
animals at Gobekli Tepe,

00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:29.430 align:middle line:84%
have led researchers to
conclude that Karahan Tepe is

00:02:29.430 --> 00:02:32.910 align:middle line:84%
much older than its younger
sister, Gobekli Tepe.

00:02:32.910 --> 00:02:37.290 align:middle line:84%
Head of excavations at
Karahan Tepe, Dr. Necmi Karul

00:02:37.290 --> 00:02:40.890 align:middle line:84%
said that 12 spots estimated
to be in the same period

00:02:40.890 --> 00:02:44.610 align:middle line:84%
as Gobekli Tepe are now known
in the region, one of which

00:02:44.610 --> 00:02:46.530 align:middle line:90%
is the Karahan Tepe.

00:02:46.530 --> 00:02:49.590 align:middle line:84%
Speaking at the 10th
International Resort Tourism

00:02:49.590 --> 00:02:52.380 align:middle line:84%
Congress, culture
and tourism minister,

00:02:52.380 --> 00:02:57.300 align:middle line:84%
Mehmet Nuri Ersoy said that an
intensive and rapid excavation

00:02:57.300 --> 00:03:00.240 align:middle line:84%
program continues
in Karahan Tepe,

00:03:00.240 --> 00:03:04.620 align:middle line:84%
which to date has yielded
250 obelisks featuring animal

00:03:04.620 --> 00:03:05.760 align:middle line:90%
figures.

00:03:05.760 --> 00:03:08.880 align:middle line:84%
Ersoy claims that planned
excavations will prove

00:03:08.880 --> 00:03:12.190 align:middle line:84%
the settlement at Karahan
Tepe will be much older than

00:03:12.190 --> 00:03:15.190 align:middle line:84%
the 12,000 year
old Gobekli Tepe.

00:03:15.190 --> 00:03:17.950 align:middle line:84%
A 2016 National
Geographic article

00:03:17.950 --> 00:03:20.920 align:middle line:84%
recounted the fascinating
story of the discovery

00:03:20.920 --> 00:03:23.230 align:middle line:84%
and preservation
of Gobekli Tepe.

00:03:23.230 --> 00:03:26.290 align:middle line:10%
Professor Klaus Schmidt,
a German archeologist

00:03:26.290 --> 00:03:29.050 align:middle line:10%
who led excavations
at the site, argued

00:03:29.050 --> 00:03:33.220 align:middle line:10%
before he died in 2014 that
a vast labor force needed

00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:37.180 align:middle line:10%
to build the enclosures and that
this construction project pushed

00:03:37.180 --> 00:03:40.270 align:middle line:10%
people to develop agriculture
as a way of providing

00:03:40.270 --> 00:03:43.870 align:middle line:10%
predictable food and
perhaps drink for workers.

00:03:43.870 --> 00:03:47.810 align:middle line:84%
At the 2015 World Economic
Forum in Davos, Switzerland,

00:03:47.810 --> 00:03:50.590 align:middle line:84%
Turkey's Dogus Group
announced that they

00:03:50.590 --> 00:03:54.160 align:middle line:84%
plan to spend $50 million
over the next 20 years

00:03:54.160 --> 00:03:57.340 align:middle line:84%
in partnership with the
National Geographic Society

00:03:57.340 --> 00:03:59.380 align:middle line:90%
on the Gobekli Tepe site.

00:03:59.380 --> 00:04:02.290 align:middle line:84%
And Dogus Group chairman
Ferit Faik Sahenk,

00:04:02.290 --> 00:04:05.920 align:middle line:84%
said in a press release that the
reason so much cash was being

00:04:05.920 --> 00:04:09.580 align:middle line:84%
spent on Gobekli Tepe was
because this prehistoric temple

00:04:09.580 --> 00:04:11.810 align:middle line:90%
was the zero point in time.

00:04:11.810 --> 00:04:15.910 align:middle line:84%
Karahan Tepe may well be
Gobekli Tepe's older sister.

00:04:15.910 --> 00:04:19.540 align:middle line:84%
While Gobekli Tepe holds the
world record in media headlines

00:04:19.540 --> 00:04:22.450 align:middle line:84%
and elsewhere as the earliest
temple of its type ever

00:04:22.450 --> 00:04:25.150 align:middle line:84%
discovered, there are
several other contenders

00:04:25.150 --> 00:04:26.950 align:middle line:90%
for this crown in Turkey.

00:04:26.950 --> 00:04:29.560 align:middle line:84%
According to Jens
Notroff, an archeologist

00:04:29.560 --> 00:04:32.170 align:middle line:84%
at the German
Archeological Institute who

00:04:32.170 --> 00:04:36.620 align:middle line:84%
is working on Gobekli Tepe site,
smaller versions of the pillars,

00:04:36.620 --> 00:04:40.360 align:middle line:84%
symbols, and architecture
carved into stone Gobekli Tepe

00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:45.100 align:middle line:84%
have been found in settlements
up to 125 miles away, including

00:04:45.100 --> 00:04:46.630 align:middle line:90%
Karahan Tepe.

00:04:46.630 --> 00:04:49.510 align:middle line:84%
Professor Notroff told
National Geographic

00:04:49.510 --> 00:04:52.060 align:middle line:84%
that Gobekli Tepe
probably served the region

00:04:52.060 --> 00:04:55.600 align:middle line:84%
as a cathedral, and therefore
the surrounding sacred sites

00:04:55.600 --> 00:04:57.430 align:middle line:90%
were like parish churches.

00:04:57.430 --> 00:05:00.430 align:middle line:10%
The scientist also thinks
hunter gatherers traveled

00:05:00.430 --> 00:05:03.760 align:middle line:10%
long distances to meet,
worship, and help build

00:05:03.760 --> 00:05:06.910 align:middle line:10%
new monumental structures
through vast community

00:05:06.910 --> 00:05:11.420 align:middle line:10%
projects that included grand
feasts to display wealth.

00:05:11.420 --> 00:05:15.590 align:middle line:84%
Returning to Karahan Tepe,
according to a report in "Daily

00:05:15.590 --> 00:05:19.340 align:middle line:84%
Sabah," many more years of
excavations and research must be

00:05:19.340 --> 00:05:23.040 align:middle line:84%
conducted to determine what
exactly it was used for.

00:05:23.040 --> 00:05:26.150 align:middle line:84%
However, while it does
happen, scientists seldom

00:05:26.150 --> 00:05:29.000 align:middle line:84%
make big claims without
equally big proof.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.300 align:middle line:84%
And in this instance, the
researchers think that when they

00:05:32.300 --> 00:05:36.000 align:middle line:84%
ultimately get to Karahan
Tepe's excavation center,

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:39.230 align:middle line:84%
it will be much older
than 12,000 years.

00:05:39.230 --> 00:05:41.690 align:middle line:84%
The archeologists
at Karahan Tepe

00:05:41.690 --> 00:05:44.330 align:middle line:84%
are also convinced that
they have a new zero

00:05:44.330 --> 00:05:45.960 align:middle line:90%
point in World history.

00:05:45.960 --> 00:05:49.310 align:middle line:84%
The mayor says the site will
become a priority in place

00:05:49.310 --> 00:05:51.350 align:middle line:84%
of Gobekli Tepe
and it will become

00:05:51.350 --> 00:05:54.620 align:middle line:84%
a new focus of national
archeological and tourist

00:05:54.620 --> 00:05:55.760 align:middle line:90%
attention.

00:05:55.760 --> 00:05:59.990 align:middle line:84%
Karahan Tepe is the sister
to the enigmatic Gobekli Tepe

00:05:59.990 --> 00:06:03.380 align:middle line:84%
that sits around 23 miles
southeast of Gobekli

00:06:03.380 --> 00:06:06.030 align:middle line:84%
upon an elevated
limestone ridge.

00:06:06.030 --> 00:06:09.330 align:middle line:84%
It has many striking
similarities to Gobekli.

00:06:09.330 --> 00:06:14.490 align:middle line:84%
Firstly, it consists of
T-shaped pillars, 266 of them

00:06:14.490 --> 00:06:16.930 align:middle line:90%
that mostly form parallel rows.

00:06:16.930 --> 00:06:19.020 align:middle line:84%
The pillars have
relief carvings,

00:06:19.020 --> 00:06:21.210 align:middle line:84%
and the site appears
like Gobekli,

00:06:21.210 --> 00:06:25.060 align:middle line:84%
to be deliberately buried
under a great artificial mound.

00:06:25.060 --> 00:06:29.070 align:middle line:84%
Although this could be
natural as after 10,500 years

00:06:29.070 --> 00:06:32.790 align:middle line:84%
of accumulation of dirt combined
with high winds could have

00:06:32.790 --> 00:06:34.380 align:middle line:90%
covered it back up.

00:06:34.380 --> 00:06:36.800 align:middle line:10%
The comparisons
do not end there.

00:06:36.800 --> 00:06:40.350 align:middle line:84%
It also has serpent relief
carvings, strange rock

00:06:40.350 --> 00:06:44.370 align:middle line:84%
indentations, large cut
marks, porthole stones,

00:06:44.370 --> 00:06:46.560 align:middle line:84%
and an unfinished
T-shaped pillar

00:06:46.560 --> 00:06:49.505 align:middle line:84%
still in the quarry, the
focus of this article.

00:06:49.505 --> 00:07:02.320 align:middle line:90%


00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:05.800 align:middle line:84%
Karahan Tepe was first
discovered in 1997

00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:09.650 align:middle line:84%
and was surveyed in
2000 and again in 2011.

00:07:09.650 --> 00:07:13.030 align:middle line:84%
Like Gobekli Tepe, it's
located within the boundaries

00:07:13.030 --> 00:07:17.270 align:middle line:84%
of Sanliurfa, ancient Edessa,
the birthplace of Abraham

00:07:17.270 --> 00:07:19.510 align:middle line:90%
around 30 miles from the city.

00:07:19.510 --> 00:07:22.610 align:middle line:84%
It's not an officially
recognized tourist site,

00:07:22.610 --> 00:07:24.700 align:middle line:84%
so they had to plan
their trip carefully

00:07:24.700 --> 00:07:28.310 align:middle line:84%
as it was on private land
upon the Tektek mountains.

00:07:28.310 --> 00:07:32.080 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, a well placed,
probably modern standing stone

00:07:32.080 --> 00:07:34.180 align:middle line:84%
marked the entrance
to the track that

00:07:34.180 --> 00:07:37.060 align:middle line:84%
led to the farm that
is located behind.

00:07:37.060 --> 00:07:40.520 align:middle line:84%
When Andrew Collins
visited there in 2004,

00:07:40.520 --> 00:07:43.120 align:middle line:84%
the person who showed
him around was warned he

00:07:43.120 --> 00:07:46.690 align:middle line:84%
would get a beating if they
found anyone had visited there.

00:07:46.690 --> 00:07:50.260 align:middle line:84%
10 years later, and the owners
welcomed the occasional visitor

00:07:50.260 --> 00:07:51.890 align:middle line:90%
with tea and information.

00:07:51.890 --> 00:07:56.140 align:middle line:84%
No beatings entailed, just sweet
hot beverages and conversation

00:07:56.140 --> 00:07:58.180 align:middle line:90%
after the morning visit.

00:07:58.180 --> 00:08:00.730 align:middle line:84%
The dating of the
site is impressive

00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:05.270 align:middle line:84%
as it's dated to
8500 BC, contemporary

00:08:05.270 --> 00:08:07.610 align:middle line:84%
with the now
submerged Nevali Cori

00:08:07.610 --> 00:08:10.460 align:middle line:84%
and the later stages
of Gobekli Tepe.

00:08:10.460 --> 00:08:12.740 align:middle line:84%
There are obvious
similarities to these

00:08:12.740 --> 00:08:15.830 align:middle line:84%
and other sites in the
vicinity, but we've

00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:18.050 align:middle line:84%
heard that there was
a quarry on site where

00:08:18.050 --> 00:08:22.160 align:middle line:84%
an unfinished T-shaped pillar
still sits within the bedrock.

00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:26.060 align:middle line:84%
Kevin Fish diligently searched
for it with only one clue,

00:08:26.060 --> 00:08:29.160 align:middle line:84%
that it was directly to the
west of the main enclosure,

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:32.059 align:middle line:90%
as mentioned in the 2011 report.

00:08:32.059 --> 00:08:35.390 align:middle line:84%
Kevin eventually converged
at the impressive monolith.

00:08:35.390 --> 00:08:39.020 align:middle line:84%
It lies on a rock face sloping
30 degrees towards the setting

00:08:39.020 --> 00:08:39.890 align:middle line:90%
sun.

00:08:39.890 --> 00:08:42.799 align:middle line:84%
At 18 feet long, it would
probably been the largest

00:08:42.799 --> 00:08:44.490 align:middle line:90%
monolith at the site.

00:08:44.490 --> 00:08:47.990 align:middle line:84%
The site is not excavated yet,
so this can't be confirmed.

00:08:47.990 --> 00:08:51.330 align:middle line:84%
And weighs in at
around 30 to 40 tons.

00:08:51.330 --> 00:08:55.220 align:middle line:84%
Its downward angle on the slope
on natural exposed rock face

00:08:55.220 --> 00:08:59.330 align:middle line:84%
may have been why this was a
preferred spot to quarry from.

00:08:59.330 --> 00:09:02.430 align:middle line:84%
As archeologist
Bahattin Çelik explains,

00:09:02.430 --> 00:09:06.080 align:middle line:84%
this is quite a practical
technique with roughly chiseling

00:09:06.080 --> 00:09:08.630 align:middle line:84%
on the side of the rock
to produce a T shape,

00:09:08.630 --> 00:09:11.810 align:middle line:84%
whilst carving the other
side 40 centimeters wide

00:09:11.810 --> 00:09:13.350 align:middle line:90%
and 1 meter deep.

00:09:13.350 --> 00:09:17.060 align:middle line:84%
The solid pillar separated from
the bedrock with this technique

00:09:17.060 --> 00:09:19.490 align:middle line:84%
and can easily be
removed from the quarry

00:09:19.490 --> 00:09:21.320 align:middle line:90%
with the help of a slope.

00:09:21.320 --> 00:09:23.750 align:middle line:84%
Andrew Collins
decided to measure it,

00:09:23.750 --> 00:09:28.050 align:middle line:84%
and discovered it was indeed
18 feet, 5.5 meters in length,

00:09:28.050 --> 00:09:31.490 align:middle line:84%
with a maximum width
of 6.6 feet, 2 meters

00:09:31.490 --> 00:09:33.650 align:middle line:90%
across its T-shaped head.

00:09:33.650 --> 00:09:36.620 align:middle line:84%
This is similar in size
to the twin monoliths

00:09:36.620 --> 00:09:38.780 align:middle line:84%
at the center of
Gobekli's enclosure,

00:09:38.780 --> 00:09:42.540 align:middle line:84%
C and D. The weathering
was very bad,

00:09:42.540 --> 00:09:45.960 align:middle line:84%
much like the exposed parts of
the pillars on the main hill.

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:49.160 align:middle line:84%
However, what lies underneath
could be as well preserved

00:09:49.160 --> 00:09:50.660 align:middle line:90%
as Gobekli Tepe.

00:09:50.660 --> 00:09:53.990 align:middle line:84%
Altogether, Karahan Tepe
is a fascinating site

00:09:53.990 --> 00:09:56.720 align:middle line:84%
that begs excavation
as the significance

00:09:56.720 --> 00:10:01.490 align:middle line:84%
of the nearby Gobekli Tepe
has now hit the headlines.

00:10:01.490 --> 00:10:03.590 align:middle line:84%
After leaving the
site, the visitor

00:10:03.590 --> 00:10:07.140 align:middle line:84%
wondered if the location of the
choice of rock was significant.

00:10:07.140 --> 00:10:10.020 align:middle line:84%
Was the direction of the
quarry from the main temple

00:10:10.020 --> 00:10:13.220 align:middle line:84%
an indication of a tradition
that existed as far back

00:10:13.220 --> 00:10:15.570 align:middle line:90%
as 10,500 years ago?

00:10:15.570 --> 00:10:17.870 align:middle line:84%
Andrew Collins discussed
the possibility

00:10:17.870 --> 00:10:21.350 align:middle line:84%
that indeed it could be the
case as bringing quarried stone

00:10:21.350 --> 00:10:23.810 align:middle line:84%
from the west to the
east may represent

00:10:23.810 --> 00:10:26.240 align:middle line:84%
bringing it into
the light, sunrise

00:10:26.240 --> 00:10:28.470 align:middle line:90%
from darkness, the sunset.

00:10:28.470 --> 00:10:30.950 align:middle line:84%
However, the remaining
14 foot pillar

00:10:30.950 --> 00:10:34.840 align:middle line:84%
still on the eastern slope had
further avenues slightly further

00:10:34.840 --> 00:10:35.640 align:middle line:90%
East of it.

00:10:35.640 --> 00:10:39.800 align:middle line:84%
So again, it showed a possible
west to east movement.

00:10:39.800 --> 00:10:43.040 align:middle line:84%
Alternatively, it could also
represent an east to west

00:10:43.040 --> 00:10:46.910 align:middle line:84%
direction from the smaller
quarry to the main enclosure.

00:10:46.910 --> 00:10:49.770 align:middle line:84%
After searching through
some masonic texts,

00:10:49.770 --> 00:10:52.130 align:middle line:84%
a reference was
found to a ceremony

00:10:52.130 --> 00:10:56.610 align:middle line:84%
where the initiate had to move
in that direction, east to west.

00:10:56.610 --> 00:11:00.260 align:middle line:84%
Why this is perhaps could
represent facing one's own death

00:11:00.260 --> 00:11:02.690 align:middle line:84%
as initiation
rites such as these

00:11:02.690 --> 00:11:05.700 align:middle line:84%
are often about facing
deep rooted fears.

00:11:05.700 --> 00:11:09.230 align:middle line:84%
Whether this was on the minds
of the builders of Karahan Tepe,

00:11:09.230 --> 00:11:12.950 align:middle line:84%
we'll never know, unless, of
course, the site gets excavated

00:11:12.950 --> 00:11:14.540 align:middle line:90%
and evidence emerges.

00:11:14.540 --> 00:11:17.980 align:middle line:90%
For now, we can only speculate.

00:11:17.980 --> 00:11:20.620 align:middle line:84%
Another aspect that
grabbed Andrew's attention

00:11:20.620 --> 00:11:22.900 align:middle line:84%
was the fact that the
parallel rows appeared

00:11:22.900 --> 00:11:26.710 align:middle line:84%
to be serpent-like, weaving
up or down the main hill

00:11:26.710 --> 00:11:28.700 align:middle line:90%
or from the main enclosure.

00:11:28.700 --> 00:11:31.280 align:middle line:84%
In his initial
report, Andrew stated,

00:11:31.280 --> 00:11:34.600 align:middle line:84%
"It's even possible that the
zigzagging pairs of stones

00:11:34.600 --> 00:11:38.530 align:middle line:84%
making up the stone avenues
located on the northern eastern

00:11:38.530 --> 00:11:41.900 align:middle line:84%
sides of the Tepe signify
the path of snakes,

00:11:41.900 --> 00:11:45.160 align:middle line:84%
which are seen to descend like
living energy into the valley

00:11:45.160 --> 00:11:46.010 align:middle line:90%
below."

00:11:46.010 --> 00:11:48.640 align:middle line:84%
This idea is given
credence through the fact

00:11:48.640 --> 00:11:52.450 align:middle line:84%
that carving on the stone
seems directed up the hill as

00:11:52.450 --> 00:11:54.520 align:middle line:84%
if the direction of
movement is downward

00:11:54.520 --> 00:11:56.660 align:middle line:84%
through the various
sets of gateways.

00:11:56.660 --> 00:11:58.690 align:middle line:84%
After coming to this
conclusion, Andrew

00:11:58.690 --> 00:12:01.610 align:middle line:84%
dreamed of snakes, their
tails tied together,

00:12:01.610 --> 00:12:04.660 align:middle line:84%
each one trying to break free
of its bondage, all of them

00:12:04.660 --> 00:12:06.630 align:middle line:90%
writhing about in the process.

00:12:06.630 --> 00:12:08.500 align:middle line:84%
With this dream
came the impression

00:12:08.500 --> 00:12:12.820 align:middle line:84%
that the snakes represented the
containment, flow, and energy

00:12:12.820 --> 00:12:14.500 align:middle line:84%
of these stones
avenues at Karahan

00:12:14.500 --> 00:12:18.470 align:middle line:84%
Tepe, an interesting
concept if nothing else.

00:12:18.470 --> 00:12:20.690 align:middle line:10%
Earth energy springs
to mind as it

00:12:20.690 --> 00:12:23.810 align:middle line:10%
has been found in Avebury,
Brittany and Cornwall

00:12:23.810 --> 00:12:27.200 align:middle line:10%
that stone avenues mark the
path of telluric Earth energy

00:12:27.200 --> 00:12:29.600 align:middle line:10%
currents with a
crossing point often

00:12:29.600 --> 00:12:33.020 align:middle line:10%
at the center of the complex,
which would naturally congregate

00:12:33.020 --> 00:12:34.230 align:middle line:10%
on a hilltop.

00:12:34.230 --> 00:12:36.290 align:middle line:84%
More research needs
to be carried out

00:12:36.290 --> 00:12:38.250 align:middle line:90%
to confirm this hypothesis.

00:12:38.250 --> 00:12:41.850 align:middle line:84%
But with the serpent symbolism
at such a remote site,

00:12:41.850 --> 00:12:45.620 align:middle line:84%
it could even reveal the origins
of geomancy and Earth energy

00:12:45.620 --> 00:12:46.430 align:middle line:90%
science.

00:12:46.430 --> 00:12:48.680 align:middle line:84%
When they go back
in September, they

00:12:48.680 --> 00:12:51.440 align:middle line:84%
will have some equipment to
take readings and dowsing

00:12:51.440 --> 00:12:54.310 align:middle line:84%
rods to find out if
this is the case.

00:12:54.310 --> 00:12:59.980 align:middle line:90%


00:12:59.980 --> 00:13:02.320 align:middle line:84%
Divers working on
a submarine project

00:13:02.320 --> 00:13:05.460 align:middle line:84%
in McDonald Lake in the
Haliburton Forest and Wildlife

00:13:05.460 --> 00:13:06.260 align:middle line:90%
Reserve.

00:13:06.260 --> 00:13:10.540 align:middle line:84%
Ontario, Canada, discovered a
submerged manmade ancient stone

00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:15.460 align:middle line:84%
structure, possibly 5,000
to 10,000 years old.

00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:17.980 align:middle line:84%
For some, this is
irrefutable evidence

00:13:17.980 --> 00:13:21.040 align:middle line:84%
of a long lost civilization
that inhabited the region

00:13:21.040 --> 00:13:23.050 align:middle line:90%
before the last ice age.

00:13:23.050 --> 00:13:25.750 align:middle line:84%
One or two researchers
have linked the discovery

00:13:25.750 --> 00:13:30.460 align:middle line:84%
to Canada's Stonehenge, a huge
5,000 year old stone wheel

00:13:30.460 --> 00:13:32.650 align:middle line:90%
discovered South of Alberta.

00:13:32.650 --> 00:13:34.450 align:middle line:84%
Who were the people
who constructed

00:13:34.450 --> 00:13:36.160 align:middle line:90%
these mysterious monuments?

00:13:36.160 --> 00:13:39.030 align:middle line:90%
And what do they represent?

00:13:39.030 --> 00:13:42.030 align:middle line:84%
The Haliburton Forest and
Wildlife Reserve Limited

00:13:42.030 --> 00:13:46.200 align:middle line:84%
is a privately-owned forest
comprising 120 square miles

00:13:46.200 --> 00:13:49.450 align:middle line:84%
in Haliburton County,
Ontario, Canada.

00:13:49.450 --> 00:13:53.880 align:middle line:84%
The owner-manager of the
25,000-hectare Haliburton Forest

00:13:53.880 --> 00:13:58.450 align:middle line:84%
is Dr. Peter Schleifenbaum who
inherited it from his father.

00:13:58.450 --> 00:14:01.110 align:middle line:84%
Recently, various
sources on the net

00:14:01.110 --> 00:14:03.660 align:middle line:84%
carried a story about
a submarine survey

00:14:03.660 --> 00:14:07.140 align:middle line:84%
of McDonald Lake, a popular
tourist attraction, which

00:14:07.140 --> 00:14:09.850 align:middle line:90%
apparently took place in 2008.

00:14:09.850 --> 00:14:12.550 align:middle line:84%
According to the story,
during the survey,

00:14:12.550 --> 00:14:15.400 align:middle line:84%
divers encountered an
ancient stone structure,

00:14:15.400 --> 00:14:17.730 align:middle line:84%
which was thought to be
proof of the presence

00:14:17.730 --> 00:14:21.840 align:middle line:84%
of a mysterious ancient culture
in the area, life from Central

00:14:21.840 --> 00:14:23.740 align:middle line:90%
Ontario ancestors.

00:14:23.740 --> 00:14:27.120 align:middle line:84%
Staff at the Haliburton
Forest and Wildlife Reserve

00:14:27.120 --> 00:14:30.540 align:middle line:84%
would often see this unusual
stone structure balanced

00:14:30.540 --> 00:14:34.140 align:middle line:84%
on the top of a rock ledge
at a depth of about 40 feet

00:14:34.140 --> 00:14:36.930 align:middle line:84%
below the present lake
level whilst in the tours

00:14:36.930 --> 00:14:38.950 align:middle line:84%
submarine, which
was in existence

00:14:38.950 --> 00:14:41.110 align:middle line:90%
for a few years at the site.

00:14:41.110 --> 00:14:44.800 align:middle line:84%
The structure consists of
a 1,000 pound elongated

00:14:44.800 --> 00:14:49.000 align:middle line:84%
south-pointing rock, sitting on
a baseball-sized stone at each

00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:52.340 align:middle line:84%
side, which in turn
rested on a massive slab.

00:14:52.340 --> 00:14:55.810 align:middle line:84%
Initially, the structure was
considered a complex version

00:14:55.810 --> 00:14:59.500 align:middle line:84%
of a glacial erratic, rocks
carried by glaciers thousands

00:14:59.500 --> 00:15:01.660 align:middle line:84%
of years ago and left
where they happened

00:15:01.660 --> 00:15:04.580 align:middle line:84%
to melt at the end of one
of the recent ice ages.

00:15:04.580 --> 00:15:07.780 align:middle line:84%
However, when various
geologists and archeologists

00:15:07.780 --> 00:15:11.110 align:middle line:84%
examined images on the
subject, some expressed doubts

00:15:11.110 --> 00:15:13.130 align:middle line:90%
about its natural origin.

00:15:13.130 --> 00:15:15.430 align:middle line:84%
The main objection
was that the structure

00:15:15.430 --> 00:15:17.990 align:middle line:84%
has straight edges
rather than rounded,

00:15:17.990 --> 00:15:19.600 align:middle line:84%
which would normally
characterize

00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:21.650 align:middle line:90%
rock scoured by glaciers.

00:15:21.650 --> 00:15:24.310 align:middle line:84%
One alternative was that
the mysterious structure

00:15:24.310 --> 00:15:25.490 align:middle line:90%
was manmade.

00:15:25.490 --> 00:15:28.580 align:middle line:84%
But the problem was, how
could that be established?

00:15:28.580 --> 00:15:31.660 align:middle line:84%
The Haliburton Forest and
Wildlife Reserve Limited

00:15:31.660 --> 00:15:35.260 align:middle line:84%
decided to hire an underwater
archeologist to examine

00:15:35.260 --> 00:15:36.970 align:middle line:90%
the structure more closely.

00:15:36.970 --> 00:15:40.040 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, after a brief
examination of the structure,

00:15:40.040 --> 00:15:42.280 align:middle line:84%
this unnamed
archeologist concluded

00:15:42.280 --> 00:15:45.280 align:middle line:84%
that it was undoubtedly the
result of human activity

00:15:45.280 --> 00:15:47.540 align:middle line:84%
rather than an
accident of nature.

00:15:47.540 --> 00:15:50.050 align:middle line:84%
The company also
employed a statistician

00:15:50.050 --> 00:15:52.630 align:middle line:84%
to calculate the probability
of these seven rocks

00:15:52.630 --> 00:15:55.060 align:middle line:84%
in the lake falling
on top of each other

00:15:55.060 --> 00:15:57.670 align:middle line:84%
to create what looked
like a structure.

00:15:57.670 --> 00:16:00.490 align:middle line:84%
The statistician determined
that the probability

00:16:00.490 --> 00:16:03.070 align:middle line:84%
of seven rocks falling
into such positions

00:16:03.070 --> 00:16:06.680 align:middle line:84%
at the right time and place
was almost impossible.

00:16:06.680 --> 00:16:09.530 align:middle line:84%
But if the structure was
manmade, what was it?

00:16:09.530 --> 00:16:11.200 align:middle line:90%
Who built it and when?

00:16:11.200 --> 00:16:14.770 align:middle line:84%
Some researchers think it
resembled the prehistoric stone

00:16:14.770 --> 00:16:18.410 align:middle line:84%
cairns found throughout the
world, which serve as monuments,

00:16:18.410 --> 00:16:22.240 align:middle line:84%
burial sites, markers for
ceremonial land, or even

00:16:22.240 --> 00:16:23.990 align:middle line:90%
navigational aids.

00:16:23.990 --> 00:16:28.240 align:middle line:84%
Others think it may be a burial
chamber or perhaps a dolmen.

00:16:28.240 --> 00:16:32.090 align:middle line:84%
Dolmens are a type of single
chamber megalithic tomb,

00:16:32.090 --> 00:16:37.150 align:middle line:84%
mostly dating from the early
Neolithic, 4000 to 3000 BC,

00:16:37.150 --> 00:16:40.040 align:middle line:84%
found in a variety of
places throughout the world,

00:16:40.040 --> 00:16:42.730 align:middle line:84%
but mostly in Northwest
Europe, particularly

00:16:42.730 --> 00:16:46.390 align:middle line:84%
in the region of Brittany,
France, Britain, and Ireland.

00:16:46.390 --> 00:16:48.400 align:middle line:84%
The thick layer of
silt covering some

00:16:48.400 --> 00:16:50.170 align:middle line:84%
of the surfaces
of the structures

00:16:50.170 --> 00:16:52.250 align:middle line:90%
indicate that they are very old.

00:16:52.250 --> 00:16:54.500 align:middle line:84%
But beyond that, without
further evidence,

00:16:54.500 --> 00:16:57.340 align:middle line:84%
it was impossible to
say when it was built.

00:16:57.340 --> 00:17:00.620 align:middle line:84%
However, when geologists
were consulted on the matter,

00:17:00.620 --> 00:17:02.660 align:middle line:84%
they apparently
pointed to a drought,

00:17:02.660 --> 00:17:07.180 align:middle line:84%
which may have hit Eastern North
America between 9000 and 7000

00:17:07.180 --> 00:17:08.230 align:middle line:90%
BC.

00:17:08.230 --> 00:17:10.720 align:middle line:84%
At this time,
conditions were so dry

00:17:10.720 --> 00:17:12.790 align:middle line:84%
that water levels
in the Great Lakes

00:17:12.790 --> 00:17:15.440 align:middle line:90%
were as much as 165 feet lower.

00:17:15.440 --> 00:17:17.650 align:middle line:84%
And inland lakes
like McDonald Lake

00:17:17.650 --> 00:17:20.109 align:middle line:84%
may well have been at
least 40 feet lower

00:17:20.109 --> 00:17:22.060 align:middle line:90%
than their current levels.

00:17:22.060 --> 00:17:24.339 align:middle line:84%
If the structure of
the McDonald Lake

00:17:24.339 --> 00:17:26.690 align:middle line:84%
is a prehistoric
monument of some kind,

00:17:26.690 --> 00:17:29.780 align:middle line:84%
why was it situated in
such a remote place?

00:17:29.780 --> 00:17:33.670 align:middle line:84%
One theory is that the sparse
local population at the time

00:17:33.670 --> 00:17:36.830 align:middle line:84%
may have been attracted
to the spot by lake trout,

00:17:36.830 --> 00:17:39.650 align:middle line:84%
often described
as glacial relict,

00:17:39.650 --> 00:17:42.100 align:middle line:84%
as they are a holdover
from the ice age

00:17:42.100 --> 00:17:45.380 align:middle line:84%
and live mainly in deep
cold water habitats.

00:17:45.380 --> 00:17:48.710 align:middle line:84%
One geologist suggested
that in prehistoric times,

00:17:48.710 --> 00:17:50.960 align:middle line:84%
McDonald Lake was
not a lake at all,

00:17:50.960 --> 00:17:53.650 align:middle line:84%
but part of an ancient
river system, which made

00:17:53.650 --> 00:17:56.030 align:middle line:90%
an ideal habitat for the trout.

00:17:56.030 --> 00:17:59.530 align:middle line:84%
But no prehistoric monuments
of the cairn or dolmen type

00:17:59.530 --> 00:18:02.560 align:middle line:84%
exist in the USA,
Canada, or anywhere else

00:18:02.560 --> 00:18:07.420 align:middle line:84%
in the world dated to
anywhere near 9000 to 7000 BC.

00:18:07.420 --> 00:18:10.320 align:middle line:84%
Does that make this structure
the oldest in the world?

00:18:10.320 --> 00:18:14.350 align:middle line:84%
Or should the glacial, erratic
theory be examined further?

00:18:14.350 --> 00:18:17.470 align:middle line:84%
However attractive these
explanations for the Lake

00:18:17.470 --> 00:18:20.440 align:middle line:84%
McDonald structure being a
prehistoric monument are,

00:18:20.440 --> 00:18:24.130 align:middle line:84%
without further evidence
obtained in an independent study

00:18:24.130 --> 00:18:27.610 align:middle line:84%
or excavation unconnected
with the Haliburton Forest

00:18:27.610 --> 00:18:31.210 align:middle line:84%
and Wildlife Reserve Limited
such as contemporary artifacts

00:18:31.210 --> 00:18:34.520 align:middle line:84%
or signs of manmade tooling
marks on the stones,

00:18:34.520 --> 00:18:36.850 align:middle line:90%
we cannot say this for sure.

00:18:36.850 --> 00:18:39.040 align:middle line:84%
There are one or
two researchers who

00:18:39.040 --> 00:18:40.570 align:middle line:84%
have linked the
underwater structure

00:18:40.570 --> 00:18:43.570 align:middle line:84%
at Lake McDonald to a
mysterious monument known

00:18:43.570 --> 00:18:45.410 align:middle line:90%
as Canada's Stonehenge.

00:18:45.410 --> 00:18:48.580 align:middle line:10%
This would make the Lake
McDonald prehistoric structure

00:18:48.580 --> 00:18:52.570 align:middle line:10%
later in date, say, around
3000 BC, though still

00:18:52.570 --> 00:18:54.400 align:middle line:10%
unique to the area.

00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:58.090 align:middle line:10%
In his 2008 book,
"Canada's Stonehenge,

00:18:58.090 --> 00:19:01.780 align:middle line:10%
Astounding Archeological
Discoveries in Canada, England,

00:19:01.780 --> 00:19:05.980 align:middle line:10%
and Wales," author Gordon R.
Freeman puts forward the theory

00:19:05.980 --> 00:19:09.470 align:middle line:84%
that the ancient structure
is a prehistoric calendar.

00:19:09.470 --> 00:19:12.640 align:middle line:84%
A summary of the book on
Freeman's website states,

00:19:12.640 --> 00:19:16.810 align:middle line:84%
"The discovery of a $5,000 year
old sun temple and an ancient

00:19:16.810 --> 00:19:20.980 align:middle line:84%
time machine, Stonehenge
calendar in Canada led scientist

00:19:20.980 --> 00:19:24.850 align:middle line:84%
Gordon Freeman to groundbreaking
discoveries in Stonehenge."

00:19:24.850 --> 00:19:29.450 align:middle line:84%
During fieldwork and
research from 1986 to 2006,

00:19:29.450 --> 00:19:32.920 align:middle line:84%
Freeman found striking
similarities between the surface

00:19:32.920 --> 00:19:35.180 align:middle line:90%
geometry of the two sites.

00:19:35.180 --> 00:19:38.630 align:middle line:84%
These similarities push back the
boundaries of written history

00:19:38.630 --> 00:19:40.640 align:middle line:84%
and have far
reaching implications

00:19:40.640 --> 00:19:44.180 align:middle line:84%
for North American
and European history.

00:19:44.180 --> 00:19:46.880 align:middle line:84%
Could the same mysterious
ancient cultures

00:19:46.880 --> 00:19:50.970 align:middle line:84%
have built Canada's Stonehenge
and the Lake McDonald structure?

00:19:50.970 --> 00:19:53.840 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps they were both related
to ancient astronomical

00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:55.220 align:middle line:90%
observations.

00:19:55.220 --> 00:19:57.260 align:middle line:84%
Freeman describes
what he discovered

00:19:57.260 --> 00:20:01.370 align:middle line:84%
at the ancient site of Canada's
Stonehenge, located in Vulcan

00:20:01.370 --> 00:20:03.260 align:middle line:90%
County, Alberta, in his book.

00:20:03.260 --> 00:20:06.560 align:middle line:84%
"I have found an amazingly
accurate year-round calendar

00:20:06.560 --> 00:20:11.180 align:middle line:84%
in this sun temple, marked with
rock lines pointing to sun rises

00:20:11.180 --> 00:20:13.440 align:middle line:90%
and sets at critical dates.

00:20:13.440 --> 00:20:16.460 align:middle line:84%
I later learned of arguments
going on, mainly negative,

00:20:16.460 --> 00:20:19.430 align:middle line:84%
about whether Stonehenge
contained marked observation

00:20:19.430 --> 00:20:23.210 align:middle line:84%
lines to the summer solstice
sunrise and the winter solstice

00:20:23.210 --> 00:20:24.300 align:middle line:90%
sunset.

00:20:24.300 --> 00:20:27.920 align:middle line:84%
By applying what I had learned
in Alberta to observing sun

00:20:27.920 --> 00:20:30.300 align:middle line:84%
rises and sets
through Stonehenge,

00:20:30.300 --> 00:20:34.460 align:middle line:84%
I found that an accurate entire
year-round calendar exists

00:20:34.460 --> 00:20:36.680 align:middle line:90%
in Stonehenge."

00:20:36.680 --> 00:20:38.960 align:middle line:84%
The term Canada's
Stonehenge refers

00:20:38.960 --> 00:20:42.050 align:middle line:84%
to the monument known by
archeologists and historians

00:20:42.050 --> 00:20:44.810 align:middle line:90%
as Majorville Medicine Wheel.

00:20:44.810 --> 00:20:49.370 align:middle line:84%
There are between 70 and 150
Native American stone structures

00:20:49.370 --> 00:20:53.390 align:middle line:84%
known as medicine wheels spread
over the Northern United States

00:20:53.390 --> 00:20:54.920 align:middle line:90%
and Southern Canada.

00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:57.330 align:middle line:10%
Though each individual
structure is unique,

00:20:57.330 --> 00:20:59.960 align:middle line:10%
the shape of the most common
type of medicine wheel

00:20:59.960 --> 00:21:03.020 align:middle line:10%
resembles that of a wagon
wheel lying on its side,

00:21:03.020 --> 00:21:06.380 align:middle line:10%
with a central cairn from which
lines of cobblestone radiate

00:21:06.380 --> 00:21:09.620 align:middle line:10%
outwards to a surrounding
ring of stones.

00:21:09.620 --> 00:21:13.040 align:middle line:84%
The diameter of medicine wheels
as well as the number and length

00:21:13.040 --> 00:21:15.000 align:middle line:90%
of their spokes varies.

00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:17.180 align:middle line:84%
The largest so far
discovered, has

00:21:17.180 --> 00:21:19.610 align:middle line:90%
a diameter of around 80 feet.

00:21:19.610 --> 00:21:22.850 align:middle line:84%
Occasionally, there will be a
break in the outer stone circle

00:21:22.850 --> 00:21:26.360 align:middle line:84%
to allow a stone pathway
or entrance into the center

00:21:26.360 --> 00:21:27.480 align:middle line:90%
of the structure.

00:21:27.480 --> 00:21:30.440 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes one of the spokes
can be considerably longer

00:21:30.440 --> 00:21:32.540 align:middle line:84%
than the others,
perhaps signifying

00:21:32.540 --> 00:21:35.630 align:middle line:84%
the importance of the direction
in which it's pointing.

00:21:35.630 --> 00:21:39.400 align:middle line:84%
The dates of these medicine
wheels also vary considerably,

00:21:39.400 --> 00:21:43.230 align:middle line:84%
but it is acknowledged that the
oldest so far investigated is

00:21:43.230 --> 00:21:47.340 align:middle line:84%
the Majorville Medicine Wheel,
which was started around 5,500

00:21:47.340 --> 00:21:48.450 align:middle line:90%
years ago.

00:21:48.450 --> 00:21:50.160 align:middle line:84%
There is no doubt
that the wheel may

00:21:50.160 --> 00:21:52.600 align:middle line:84%
have served some
astronomical function,

00:21:52.600 --> 00:21:54.360 align:middle line:84%
but it is more
probable that this

00:21:54.360 --> 00:21:56.890 align:middle line:84%
would have been part
of a wider ritual use,

00:21:56.890 --> 00:22:00.660 align:middle line:84%
perhaps involving hunting,
magic, or buffalo fertility.

00:22:00.660 --> 00:22:04.290 align:middle line:10%
This is not to say that Native
Americans were not sophisticated

00:22:04.290 --> 00:22:08.310 align:middle line:10%
enough to build observatories,
far from it, but in one sense,

00:22:08.310 --> 00:22:11.550 align:middle line:10%
to state that the Majorville
Medicine Wheel was built only

00:22:11.550 --> 00:22:15.750 align:middle line:10%
to make complex astronomical
calculations is to apply modern

00:22:15.750 --> 00:22:20.100 align:middle line:10%
Western ideas from a 21st
century technology-dominated era

00:22:20.100 --> 00:22:21.760 align:middle line:10%
back into the past.

00:22:21.760 --> 00:22:24.660 align:middle line:84%
This explanation
reflects our own concerns

00:22:24.660 --> 00:22:28.330 align:middle line:84%
with timekeeping, calendars,
computers, and space,

00:22:28.330 --> 00:22:31.110 align:middle line:84%
not necessarily those
of the Native Americans

00:22:31.110 --> 00:22:33.916 align:middle line:84%
who built and used
Canada's Stonehenge.

