back at least 7,000 years with

00:23:06.150 --> 00:23:08.850 align:middle line:84%
a wide range of
archeological remains,

00:23:08.850 --> 00:23:11.790 align:middle line:84%
from the megalithic temples
and underground chambers

00:23:11.790 --> 00:23:15.450 align:middle line:84%
of prehistory to the Baroque
architecture of the medieval

00:23:15.450 --> 00:23:16.770 align:middle line:90%
period.

00:23:16.770 --> 00:23:20.400 align:middle line:84%
The most spectacular and
enigmatic of the ancient remains

00:23:20.400 --> 00:23:25.110 align:middle line:84%
on Malta are the Neolithic
temples and tombs built 1,000

00:23:25.110 --> 00:23:27.270 align:middle line:90%
years before the pyramids.

00:23:27.270 --> 00:23:30.960 align:middle line:84%
And Malta has the oldest
free-standing stone buildings

00:23:30.960 --> 00:23:32.520 align:middle line:90%
in the world.

00:23:32.520 --> 00:23:34.920 align:middle line:84%
One of the most
fascinating and mysterious

00:23:34.920 --> 00:23:37.230 align:middle line:84%
of these megalithic
structures is known

00:23:37.230 --> 00:23:40.980 align:middle line:90%
as the Hal-Saflieni hypogeum.

00:23:40.980 --> 00:23:44.260 align:middle line:10%
A hypogeum is a subterranean
rock-cut chamber

00:23:44.260 --> 00:23:46.120 align:middle line:10%
of an ancient
building, and there

00:23:46.120 --> 00:23:48.160 align:middle line:10%
are a number of these
type of monuments spread

00:23:48.160 --> 00:23:52.520 align:middle line:10%
across the Mediterranean
in Southern France, Sicily,

00:23:52.520 --> 00:23:54.760 align:middle line:10%
Sardinia, and Crete.

00:23:54.760 --> 00:23:58.660 align:middle line:84%
The Hal-Saflieni hypogeum is
an underground tomb and temple

00:23:58.660 --> 00:24:04.330 align:middle line:84%
complex extending for
around 5380 square feet,

00:24:04.330 --> 00:24:07.360 align:middle line:84%
and is located in the
town of Paola, which is

00:24:07.360 --> 00:24:10.120 align:middle line:90%
in the south of Malta island.

00:24:10.120 --> 00:24:13.720 align:middle line:84%
The site was discovered
by accident in 1902

00:24:13.720 --> 00:24:16.300 align:middle line:84%
when workers digging
cisterns for new houses

00:24:16.300 --> 00:24:19.670 align:middle line:84%
above broke through the
roof of one of the chambers.

00:24:19.670 --> 00:24:21.820 align:middle line:84%
The first excavations
at the site

00:24:21.820 --> 00:24:23.710 align:middle line:84%
were performed by
Father Emmanuel

00:24:23.710 --> 00:24:27.400 align:middle line:84%
Magri of the Society of
Jesus and later continued

00:24:27.400 --> 00:24:31.330 align:middle line:84%
by Dr. Temi Zammit, the first
curator of Malta's museums

00:24:31.330 --> 00:24:32.410 align:middle line:90%
department.

00:24:32.410 --> 00:24:36.820 align:middle line:84%
Between 1905 and
1911, Zammit excavated

00:24:36.820 --> 00:24:39.610 align:middle line:84%
a fascinating collection
of Archeological material

00:24:39.610 --> 00:24:44.810 align:middle line:84%
from the complex, including
human remains, pottery, beads,

00:24:44.810 --> 00:24:46.600 align:middle line:90%
amulets, and figurines.

00:24:46.600 --> 00:24:48.720 align:middle line:84%
And he wrote a series
of reports of his work

00:24:48.720 --> 00:24:52.240 align:middle line:84%
at the site that was
published from 1910 onward.

00:24:52.240 --> 00:24:55.900 align:middle line:84%
The hypogeum was first
opened to the public in 1908

00:24:55.900 --> 00:24:59.040 align:middle line:84%
while excavations were
still taking place.

00:24:59.040 --> 00:25:01.830 align:middle line:10%
The Hal-Saflieni
hypogeum consists

00:25:01.830 --> 00:25:04.500 align:middle line:10%
of a series of oval
chambers, halls,

00:25:04.500 --> 00:25:08.560 align:middle line:10%
and niches set on three levels,
one underneath the other.

00:25:08.560 --> 00:25:11.070 align:middle line:84%
Incredibly, the
underground structures

00:25:11.070 --> 00:25:15.300 align:middle line:84%
were all carved out of solid
rock in semi-darkness, allegedly

00:25:15.300 --> 00:25:18.030 align:middle line:84%
using stone mallets
and antler picks

00:25:18.030 --> 00:25:22.470 align:middle line:84%
and later smoothed over
using flint implements.

00:25:22.470 --> 00:25:25.080 align:middle line:84%
The upper level of
the complex consists

00:25:25.080 --> 00:25:28.800 align:middle line:84%
of a hollow with a central
passageway with burial chambers

00:25:28.800 --> 00:25:31.890 align:middle line:84%
cut into the natural
caves on each side.

00:25:31.890 --> 00:25:35.610 align:middle line:84%
This is the oldest level
of the hypogeum in use

00:25:35.610 --> 00:25:40.800 align:middle line:84%
from 3600 BC to 3300
BC, and is similar

00:25:40.800 --> 00:25:43.020 align:middle line:84%
and plan to earlier
rock-cut cut tombs

00:25:43.020 --> 00:25:48.160 align:middle line:84%
found elsewhere on the islands
such as the Xemxija tombs, which

00:25:48.160 --> 00:25:51.070 align:middle line:90%
date to around 4000 BC.

00:25:51.070 --> 00:25:55.480 align:middle line:84%
The middle level,
3300 to 3000 BC,

00:25:55.480 --> 00:25:59.050 align:middle line:84%
was cut into the subsurface
rock as an extension

00:25:59.050 --> 00:26:01.330 align:middle line:84%
of the upper level
of the structure.

00:26:01.330 --> 00:26:04.960 align:middle line:84%
This level exhibits
exquisite stoneworking skill

00:26:04.960 --> 00:26:07.820 align:middle line:84%
in the elaborately
carved trilithons,

00:26:07.820 --> 00:26:09.730 align:middle line:84%
which are a
construction with two

00:26:09.730 --> 00:26:13.750 align:middle line:84%
upright posts with a
horizontal one set on top.

00:26:13.750 --> 00:26:16.480 align:middle line:84%
The trilithons are
set in imitation

00:26:16.480 --> 00:26:19.090 align:middle line:84%
of the built masonry
of the above ground

00:26:19.090 --> 00:26:23.080 align:middle line:84%
megalithic structures
found elsewhere on Malta.

00:26:23.080 --> 00:26:26.950 align:middle line:84%
This level also contains some
of the most important features

00:26:26.950 --> 00:26:31.540 align:middle line:84%
of the hypogeum monument, such
as the main chamber, the Oracle

00:26:31.540 --> 00:26:34.420 align:middle line:84%
Room, and the Holy
of the Holies.

00:26:34.420 --> 00:26:37.390 align:middle line:84%
Most of the wall surfaces
in the main chamber

00:26:37.390 --> 00:26:40.010 align:middle line:84%
originally had a
wash of red ocher,

00:26:40.010 --> 00:26:43.870 align:middle line:84%
tracing out spiral and
honeycomb designs, some of which

00:26:43.870 --> 00:26:46.480 align:middle line:90%
are still visible today.

00:26:46.480 --> 00:26:51.040 align:middle line:10%
The famous Sleeping Lady, a
12 centimeter long reclining

00:26:51.040 --> 00:26:54.140 align:middle line:10%
terracotta figure with
traces of red ocher,

00:26:54.140 --> 00:26:57.220 align:middle line:10%
was recovered either from
here or a nearby room, which

00:26:57.220 --> 00:26:59.470 align:middle line:10%
is known as the Snake Pit.

00:26:59.470 --> 00:27:02.890 align:middle line:10%
Believed to date
from around 3000 BC,

00:27:02.890 --> 00:27:06.670 align:middle line:10%
this corpulent ceramic
figure is naked to the waist

00:27:06.670 --> 00:27:08.920 align:middle line:10%
and wears a fringed skirt.

00:27:08.920 --> 00:27:12.310 align:middle line:10%
She appears to be in a deep,
tranquil sleep on a bed

00:27:12.310 --> 00:27:13.880 align:middle line:10%
with a rush mattress.

00:27:13.880 --> 00:27:15.970 align:middle line:10%
Along with other
similar figurines

00:27:15.970 --> 00:27:17.950 align:middle line:10%
from the Neolithic
sites on Malta

00:27:17.950 --> 00:27:20.120 align:middle line:10%
and elsewhere in
the Mediterranean,

00:27:20.120 --> 00:27:22.540 align:middle line:10%
the sleeping lady has
been used as evidence

00:27:22.540 --> 00:27:25.210 align:middle line:10%
for the theory of universal
peace-loving mother

00:27:25.210 --> 00:27:29.560 align:middle line:10%
goddess or great goddess
worship in prehistory proposed

00:27:29.560 --> 00:27:31.480 align:middle line:10%
by a number of researchers.

00:27:31.480 --> 00:27:34.970 align:middle line:84%
One interesting theory
regarding the sleeping lady,

00:27:34.970 --> 00:27:39.650 align:middle line:84%
whether goddess or not, is that
either in a trance or asleep,

00:27:39.650 --> 00:27:42.190 align:middle line:84%
she may represent a
place in the hypogeum

00:27:42.190 --> 00:27:45.150 align:middle line:84%
where dreams or trance
visions were interpreted

00:27:45.150 --> 00:27:47.430 align:middle line:90%
by priests or priestesses.

00:27:47.430 --> 00:27:50.310 align:middle line:10%
Such a dark,
subterranean context

00:27:50.310 --> 00:27:53.310 align:middle line:10%
would have been ideal for the
stimulation of such states

00:27:53.310 --> 00:27:56.270 align:middle line:10%
as it would induce
dreams and visions.

00:27:56.270 --> 00:28:00.150 align:middle line:84%
Alternatively, because the
area was used for burials,

00:28:00.150 --> 00:28:04.060 align:middle line:84%
the statue may be a
representation of eternal sleep.

00:28:04.060 --> 00:28:06.570 align:middle line:10%
The enigmatic
sleeping lady figurine

00:28:06.570 --> 00:28:08.430 align:middle line:10%
is now on display
at the National

00:28:08.430 --> 00:28:10.960 align:middle line:10%
Museum of Archeology
in Valletta,

00:28:10.960 --> 00:28:13.410 align:middle line:10%
the capital city of Malta.

00:28:13.410 --> 00:28:17.880 align:middle line:84%
Also on the middle level, the
roughly rectangular Oracle Room

00:28:17.880 --> 00:28:20.340 align:middle line:84%
has an elaborately
decorated ceiling

00:28:20.340 --> 00:28:24.100 align:middle line:84%
of ocher-painted spirals and
a fascinating side chamber,

00:28:24.100 --> 00:28:27.090 align:middle line:84%
which has the property
to amplify and echo

00:28:27.090 --> 00:28:29.130 align:middle line:90%
a deep human voice.

00:28:29.130 --> 00:28:32.550 align:middle line:84%
This is referred to as
a resonance chamber.

00:28:32.550 --> 00:28:35.730 align:middle line:84%
Whether this intriguing
effect was intentional or not

00:28:35.730 --> 00:28:38.670 align:middle line:84%
is difficult to say,
though the possibility

00:28:38.670 --> 00:28:40.890 align:middle line:84%
that these strange
acoustics were utilized

00:28:40.890 --> 00:28:43.860 align:middle line:84%
in some religious ceremonies
performed in the chambers

00:28:43.860 --> 00:28:46.030 align:middle line:90%
is an intriguing one.

00:28:46.030 --> 00:28:50.510 align:middle line:84%
The chamber resonates at
an intriguing 111 hertz,

00:28:50.510 --> 00:28:53.860 align:middle line:84%
which is known to be
a healing frequency.

00:28:53.860 --> 00:28:56.410 align:middle line:84%
Immersing yourself
in this frequency

00:28:56.410 --> 00:28:58.780 align:middle line:84%
can help increase
the healing process

00:28:58.780 --> 00:29:01.540 align:middle line:90%
of internal and external wounds.

00:29:01.540 --> 00:29:04.720 align:middle line:84%
The Holy of the Holies is
perhaps the most elaborately

00:29:04.720 --> 00:29:07.250 align:middle line:84%
decorated room in
the whole complex,

00:29:07.250 --> 00:29:11.350 align:middle line:84%
with its trilithon door frame
and pierced stone or porthole

00:29:11.350 --> 00:29:14.140 align:middle line:84%
entrance, reflecting
the architecture

00:29:14.140 --> 00:29:17.860 align:middle line:84%
of Maltese free-standing
Neolithic monuments.

00:29:17.860 --> 00:29:20.620 align:middle line:84%
The third and lowest
level at the hypogeum

00:29:20.620 --> 00:29:24.040 align:middle line:84%
is 35 feet below
street level and has

00:29:24.040 --> 00:29:29.560 align:middle line:90%
been dated to 3150 to 2500 BC.

00:29:29.560 --> 00:29:32.290 align:middle line:10%
It consists of a
maze of chambers,

00:29:32.290 --> 00:29:33.920 align:middle line:10%
which were filled with water.

00:29:33.920 --> 00:29:36.730 align:middle line:10%
When discovered in
the early 1900s.

00:29:36.730 --> 00:29:39.940 align:middle line:84%
As there have been no finds
of either bones or artifacts

00:29:39.940 --> 00:29:42.490 align:middle line:84%
from this level, it
has been suggested

00:29:42.490 --> 00:29:45.400 align:middle line:84%
that these chambers here
may have been designed

00:29:45.400 --> 00:29:48.010 align:middle line:90%
as storage for water or grain.

00:29:48.010 --> 00:29:50.410 align:middle line:84%
Water storage has
also been put forward

00:29:50.410 --> 00:29:53.380 align:middle line:84%
as the possible function
of the hypogeum at Knossos

00:29:53.380 --> 00:29:59.500 align:middle line:84%
on Crete, dated between
2150 and 2000 BC.

00:29:59.500 --> 00:30:02.620 align:middle line:84%
The primary function of the
hypogeum site was certainly

00:30:02.620 --> 00:30:06.910 align:middle line:84%
as a cemetery, as around 7,000
skeletons have been found

00:30:06.910 --> 00:30:12.490 align:middle line:84%
in the chambers, ranging in
date from 3600 to 2500 BC,

00:30:12.490 --> 00:30:16.510 align:middle line:84%
in other words, spanning
the life of the site itself.

00:30:16.510 --> 00:30:19.780 align:middle line:84%
This amount of human remains
is significantly higher

00:30:19.780 --> 00:30:23.000 align:middle line:84%
than the tombs could have
housed at any one period,

00:30:23.000 --> 00:30:26.350 align:middle line:84%
indicating, along with the
dates of the skeletons,

00:30:26.350 --> 00:30:31.330 align:middle line:84%
that the complex was used for
burials over several centuries.

00:30:31.330 --> 00:30:34.180 align:middle line:84%
The fact that no human
remains were discovered

00:30:34.180 --> 00:30:37.540 align:middle line:84%
in some rooms such
as the Holy of Holies

00:30:37.540 --> 00:30:41.050 align:middle line:84%
would suggest other functions
for these parts of the site.

00:30:41.050 --> 00:30:44.110 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps they were used for
funerary rituals involving

00:30:44.110 --> 00:30:46.670 align:middle line:84%
priests contacting
the ancestors.

00:30:46.670 --> 00:30:49.570 align:middle line:84%
An interesting clue to one
of the original functions

00:30:49.570 --> 00:30:52.060 align:middle line:84%
of the hypogeum
is the resemblance

00:30:52.060 --> 00:30:54.230 align:middle line:90%
of the site to natural caves.

00:30:54.230 --> 00:30:57.580 align:middle line:84%
The near darkness of the
original subterranean chambers

00:30:57.580 --> 00:31:00.080 align:middle line:84%
and passageways is
a little difficult

00:31:00.080 --> 00:31:02.510 align:middle line:84%
to imagine nowadays
with the brightness

00:31:02.510 --> 00:31:04.970 align:middle line:84%
of the artificial
lighting at the site.

00:31:04.970 --> 00:31:08.390 align:middle line:84%
But originally, whoever
was allowed to venture down

00:31:08.390 --> 00:31:11.390 align:middle line:84%
into the depths of the
hypogeum would only

00:31:11.390 --> 00:31:14.090 align:middle line:84%
have had the dim light
of animal fat lamps

00:31:14.090 --> 00:31:17.920 align:middle line:84%
to help them through the maze of
rooms, passageways, and niches.

00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:21.680 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps what took place
inside the hypogeum involved

00:31:21.680 --> 00:31:24.830 align:middle line:84%
some kind of procession
or ritual initiation

00:31:24.830 --> 00:31:28.370 align:middle line:84%
through the disorienting
labyrinth structure, which

00:31:28.370 --> 00:31:31.190 align:middle line:84%
included passing through
porthole entrances

00:31:31.190 --> 00:31:34.990 align:middle line:84%
into particularly
restricted shrines.

00:31:34.990 --> 00:31:38.740 align:middle line:84%
Such a mysterious subterranean
structure as the hypogeum

00:31:38.740 --> 00:31:42.080 align:middle line:84%
is bound to generate its
own legends and folklore.

00:31:42.080 --> 00:31:45.880 align:middle line:84%
Indeed, there are a host of
legendary tales associated

00:31:45.880 --> 00:31:48.970 align:middle line:84%
with the hypogeum, from
disappearing parties

00:31:48.970 --> 00:31:52.210 align:middle line:84%
of schoolchildren to
subterranean monsters

00:31:52.210 --> 00:31:54.790 align:middle line:90%
and underground alien bases.

00:31:54.790 --> 00:31:58.060 align:middle line:10%
The majority of these stories
can be traced back to an article

00:31:58.060 --> 00:32:02.500 align:middle line:10%
by Richard Walter in the August
1940 edition of the National

00:32:02.500 --> 00:32:07.720 align:middle line:10%
Geographic Magazine entitled
"Wanderers Awheel in Malta."

00:32:07.720 --> 00:32:11.140 align:middle line:84%
This war time piece discusses
the various underground

00:32:11.140 --> 00:32:13.600 align:middle line:84%
passageways on Malta
being used as part

00:32:13.600 --> 00:32:16.700 align:middle line:84%
of the fortifications and
defense system of the island.

00:32:16.700 --> 00:32:19.120 align:middle line:84%
It also states that
at one time, it

00:32:19.120 --> 00:32:22.580 align:middle line:84%
was possible to traverse the
island using these tunnels,

00:32:22.580 --> 00:32:25.300 align:middle line:84%
but the government closed the
entrances to these tunnels

00:32:25.300 --> 00:32:27.790 align:middle line:84%
after school children
and their teachers became

00:32:27.790 --> 00:32:32.360 align:middle line:84%
lost in the labyrinth while on
a study tour and never returned.

00:32:32.360 --> 00:32:34.850 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, the
parents of the children

00:32:34.850 --> 00:32:36.980 align:middle line:84%
claimed they could hear
cries of the children

00:32:36.980 --> 00:32:40.490 align:middle line:84%
for weeks afterwards coming
from under the ground

00:32:40.490 --> 00:32:45.020 align:middle line:84%
in several parts of the island,
as if some strange phenomena was

00:32:45.020 --> 00:32:47.630 align:middle line:90%
beckoning others to their doom.

00:32:47.630 --> 00:32:50.840 align:middle line:84%
In this single article from
the National Geographic

00:32:50.840 --> 00:32:54.200 align:middle line:84%
lies the origin of a host
of contemporary folklore

00:32:54.200 --> 00:32:58.290 align:middle line:84%
about disappearances and secret
tunnels underneath the hypogeum,

00:32:58.290 --> 00:33:01.170 align:middle line:84%
which has been mostly
built up on the internet.

00:33:01.170 --> 00:33:04.850 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that the
original National Geographic

00:33:04.850 --> 00:33:08.220 align:middle line:84%
article cites no
sources for the tale,

00:33:08.220 --> 00:33:10.760 align:middle line:84%
and no contemporary
accounts of the tragedy

00:33:10.760 --> 00:33:12.680 align:middle line:90%
have ever been discovered.

00:33:12.680 --> 00:33:16.170 align:middle line:84%
The hypogeum is not mentioned
by name in the article,

00:33:16.170 --> 00:33:19.340 align:middle line:84%
so we are not even sure if
the alleged incident even

00:33:19.340 --> 00:33:20.460 align:middle line:90%
occurred there.

00:33:20.460 --> 00:33:24.860 align:middle line:84%
The story has the ring of
local folklore, perhaps a tale

00:33:24.860 --> 00:33:28.380 align:middle line:84%
concocted to keep children away
from the dangerous tunnels.

00:33:28.380 --> 00:33:31.370 align:middle line:84%
It also brings to mind the
mysterious disappearance

00:33:31.370 --> 00:33:34.920 align:middle line:84%
of the Australian schoolgirls
in Joan Lindsay's novel,

00:33:34.920 --> 00:33:39.750 align:middle line:84%
"Picnic at Hanging Rock,"
1967, for many years,

00:33:39.750 --> 00:33:43.580 align:middle line:84%
believed to be a true incident,
despite the protestations

00:33:43.580 --> 00:33:45.710 align:middle line:90%
of the author of the novel.

00:33:45.710 --> 00:33:49.880 align:middle line:10%
Thanks to a number of stories
published first in the 1960s

00:33:49.880 --> 00:33:52.490 align:middle line:10%
and copied on the internet
over the past decade

00:33:52.490 --> 00:33:56.420 align:middle line:10%
or so, the folklore of the
alleged hypogeum disappearance

00:33:56.420 --> 00:33:58.710 align:middle line:10%
has taken on a life of its own.

00:33:58.710 --> 00:34:01.760 align:middle line:84%
According to these
stories, which conveniently

00:34:01.760 --> 00:34:04.790 align:middle line:84%
don't cite any
sources, 30 children

00:34:04.790 --> 00:34:06.620 align:middle line:84%
vanished with their
teachers while

00:34:06.620 --> 00:34:09.199 align:middle line:90%
on a study tour of the hypogeum.

00:34:09.199 --> 00:34:12.230 align:middle line:84%
New elements with no
foundation in fact

00:34:12.230 --> 00:34:16.219 align:middle line:84%
whatsoever were added to the
archeology of the hypogeum

00:34:16.219 --> 00:34:20.730 align:middle line:84%
site itself to make the supposed
disappearance more lurid.

00:34:20.730 --> 00:34:24.440 align:middle line:84%
So we have 30,000 bodies
discovered by archeologists

00:34:24.440 --> 00:34:26.989 align:middle line:90%
in the chambers, not 7,000.

00:34:26.989 --> 00:34:29.870 align:middle line:84%
And the remains were
all human sacrifices

00:34:29.870 --> 00:34:32.120 align:middle line:90%
to some underworld god.

00:34:32.120 --> 00:34:34.850 align:middle line:84%
In the best traditions
of the modern folklore

00:34:34.850 --> 00:34:37.230 align:middle line:84%
of underground
archeological sites,

00:34:37.230 --> 00:34:39.350 align:middle line:84%
the tunnels underneath
the hypogeum

00:34:39.350 --> 00:34:41.750 align:middle line:84%
are said to stretch
for hundreds of miles

00:34:41.750 --> 00:34:44.810 align:middle line:84%
all the way to the
catacombs underneath Rome,

00:34:44.810 --> 00:34:48.510 align:middle line:84%
improving on the original
National Geographic article.

00:34:48.510 --> 00:34:51.230 align:middle line:84%
We are told that a
British embassy worker,

00:34:51.230 --> 00:34:53.929 align:middle line:84%
or in some accounts,
an American tourist

00:34:53.929 --> 00:34:57.590 align:middle line:84%
called Ms. Lois Jessop
discovered a series of tunnels

00:34:57.590 --> 00:35:00.390 align:middle line:84%
underneath the lower
level of the hypogeum.

00:35:00.390 --> 00:35:03.770 align:middle line:84%
And in an unexplored
cavern, she encountered

00:35:03.770 --> 00:35:07.760 align:middle line:84%
several large, hairy
creatures with strange powers.

00:35:07.760 --> 00:35:12.080 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, she later learned
that this was the same cavern

00:35:12.080 --> 00:35:14.450 align:middle line:84%
where the children and their
teachers had disappeared

00:35:14.450 --> 00:35:18.380 align:middle line:84%
sometime in the 1940s,
after which the entrance

00:35:18.380 --> 00:35:21.860 align:middle line:84%
of the hypogeum was sealed
off and nobody was allowed

00:35:21.860 --> 00:35:23.600 align:middle line:90%
to investigate the site.

00:35:23.600 --> 00:35:26.160 align:middle line:84%
From working at the
British embassy,

00:35:26.160 --> 00:35:28.520 align:middle line:84%
Ms. Lois Jessop
went on to become

00:35:28.520 --> 00:35:33.380 align:middle line:84%
secretary of the New York Flying
Saucer Information Bureau.

00:35:33.380 --> 00:35:37.640 align:middle line:84%
The sources for these bizarre
stories include a 1960s printed

00:35:37.640 --> 00:35:42.470 align:middle line:84%
lecture by one-time director
of Borderland Sciences Research

00:35:42.470 --> 00:35:47.330 align:middle line:84%
Foundation, Riley Crabb called
"The Reality of the Cavern

00:35:47.330 --> 00:35:52.280 align:middle line:84%
World" and a chapter, "Malta,
Entrance to the Cavern World"

00:35:52.280 --> 00:36:00.360 align:middle line:84%
in a 1966 book entitled "Enigma
Fantastique" by W. Gordon Allen,

00:36:00.360 --> 00:36:03.680 align:middle line:84%
essentially a reprint
of the Crabb article.

00:36:03.680 --> 00:36:06.530 align:middle line:84%
There is one element of
these bizarre legends

00:36:06.530 --> 00:36:09.750 align:middle line:84%
about the hypogeum that has
some truth to it, however.

00:36:09.750 --> 00:36:14.310 align:middle line:84%
The site was indeed closed for
a number of years between 1992

00:36:14.310 --> 00:36:18.830 align:middle line:84%
and 1996, though not because
of any mysterious disappearance

00:36:18.830 --> 00:36:20.160 align:middle line:90%
in its tunnels.

00:36:20.160 --> 00:36:23.390 align:middle line:84%
The reason was that
major conservation work

00:36:23.390 --> 00:36:25.850 align:middle line:84%
was being carried out
due to the damage being

00:36:25.850 --> 00:36:28.190 align:middle line:84%
done to the limestone
walls by years

00:36:28.190 --> 00:36:32.840 align:middle line:84%
of visitors exhaling carbon
dioxide in the enclosed space.

00:36:32.840 --> 00:36:35.650 align:middle line:84%
To protect against
this damage, numbers

00:36:35.650 --> 00:36:39.530 align:middle line:84%
are now restricted to 80
prebooked visitors per day,

00:36:39.530 --> 00:36:41.740 align:middle line:84%
and a microclimate
has been installed

00:36:41.740 --> 00:36:44.680 align:middle line:84%
above the underground chambers
to regulate air temperature

00:36:44.680 --> 00:36:45.980 align:middle line:90%
and humidity.

00:36:45.980 --> 00:36:50.230 align:middle line:84%
In 1980, the fascinating
Hal-Saflieni hypogeum

00:36:50.230 --> 00:36:53.490 align:middle line:84%
was added to UNESCO's
World Heritage list.

00:36:53.490 --> 00:36:57.540 align:middle line:84%
Strangely enough, when
now visiting the hypogeum,

00:36:57.540 --> 00:37:00.820 align:middle line:84%
visitors are not permitted
to photograph, film,

00:37:00.820 --> 00:37:04.600 align:middle line:84%
or even take audible recordings
while security guards watch

00:37:04.600 --> 00:37:08.140 align:middle line:84%
over a controlled small
group of 20 visitors.

00:37:08.140 --> 00:37:11.360 align:middle line:84%
Many researchers
ponder, why is that?

00:37:11.360 --> 00:37:16.200 align:middle line:84%
And is there something that is
being kept away from the public?

00:37:16.200 --> 00:37:17.000 align:middle line:90%